\"\nBULLET::::- 1946 – Alan Frumin, American lawyer and politician\nBULLET::::- 1946 – Tiit Rosenberg, Estonian historian and academic\nBULLET::::- 1947 – James T. Conway, American general\nBULLET::::- 1947 – Jean Echenoz, French author\nBULLET::::- 1947 – Carlton Fisk, American baseball player\nBULLET::::- 1947 – Josef Janíček, Czech singer-songwriter, guitarist, and keyboard player\nBULLET::::- 1947 – Richard Levis McCormick, American historian and academic\nBULLET::::- 1948 – Candy Crowley, American journalist\nBULLET::::- 1949 – José Ramos-Horta, East Timorese lawyer and politician, 2nd President of East Timor, Nobel Prize laureate\nBULLET::::- 1950 – Raja Pervaiz Ashraf, Pakistani businessman and politician, 17th Prime Minister of Pakistan\nBULLET::::- 1950 – Mario Mendoza, Mexican baseball player and manager\nBULLET::::- 1953 – Leonel Fernández, Dominican lawyer and politician, 51st President of the Dominican Republic\nBULLET::::- 1953 – Makis Katsavakis, Greek footballer and manager\nBULLET::::- 1953 – Toomas Hendrik Ilves, Swedish-Estonian journalist and politician, 4th President of Estonia\nBULLET::::- 1953 – Henning Schmitz, German drummer\nBULLET::::- 1954 – Peter Hillary, New Zealand mountaineer and philanthropist\nBULLET::::- 1954 – Ozzie Smith, American baseball player and sportscaster\nBULLET::::- 1955 – Evan Bayh, American lawyer and politician, 46th Governor of Indiana\nBULLET::::- 1956 – David Sedaris, American comedian, author, and radio host\nBULLET::::- 1957 – Dermot Murnaghan, English-Northern Irish journalist and game show host\nBULLET::::- 1958 – Adrian Newey, English aerodynamicist and engineer\nBULLET::::- 1959 – Kōji Morimoto, Japanese animator and director\nBULLET::::- 1959 – Hans Nielsen, Danish motorcycle racer\nBULLET::::- 1959 – Wang Lijun, Chinese police officer and politician\nBULLET::::- 1960 – Keith Martin Ball, American mathematician and academic\nBULLET::::- 1960 – Ruud Kaiser, Dutch footballer and manager\nBULLET::::- 1960 – Ji