{"id": "8386", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=8386", "title": "Dynamics", "text": "Dynamics\n\nDynamics (from Greek δυναμικός \"dynamikos\" \"powerful\", from δύναμις \"dynamis\" \"power\") or dynamic may refer to:\nBULLET::::- Dynamics (mechanics)\nBULLET::::- Aerodynamics, the study of the motion of air\nBULLET::::- Analytical dynamics, the motion of bodies as induced by external forces\nBULLET::::- Brownian dynamics, the occurrence of Langevin dynamics in the motion of particles in solution\nBULLET::::- File dynamics, stochastic motion of particles in a channel\nBULLET::::- Flight dynamics, the science of aircraft and spacecraft design\nBULLET::::- Fluid dynamics or \"hydrodynamics\", the study of fluid flow\nBULLET::::- Computational fluid dynamics, a way of studying fluid dynamics using numerical methods\nBULLET::::- Fractional dynamics, dynamics with integrations and differentiations of fractional orders\nBULLET::::- Molecular dynamics, the study of motion on the molecular level\nBULLET::::- Langevin dynamics, a mathematical model for stochastic dynamics\nBULLET::::- Orbital dynamics, the study of the motion of rockets and spacecraft\nBULLET::::- Quantum chromodynamics, a theory of the strong interaction (color force)\nBULLET::::- Quantum electrodynamics, a description of how matter and light interact\nBULLET::::- Relativistic dynamics, a combination of relativistic and quantum concepts\nBULLET::::- Stellar dynamics, a description of the collective motion of stars\nBULLET::::- System dynamics, the study of the behavior of complex systems\nBULLET::::- Thermodynamics, the study of the relationships between heat and mechanical energy\nBULLET::::- Vehicle dynamics\n\nBULLET::::- Dynamic (record label), an Italian record label in Genoa\nBULLET::::- Arrow Dynamics, roller coaster designer\nBULLET::::- Boston Dynamics, robot designer\nBULLET::::- Crystal Dynamics, video game developer\nBULLET::::- General Dynamics, defence contractor\nBULLET::::- Microso